  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "28",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Google Basemaps\n",
    "\n",
    "Due to licensing restrictions, Google basemaps are not included in geemap by default. However, users can add Google basemaps manually at their own discretion using the following URLs:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "    ROADMAP:  https://mt1.google.com/vt/lyrs=m&x={x}&y={y}&z={z}\n",
    "    SATELLITE: https://mt1.google.com/vt/lyrs=s&x={x}&y={y}&z={z}\n",
    "    TERRAIN: https://mt1.google.com/vt/lyrs=p&x={x}&y={y}&z={z}\n",
    "    HYBRID: https://mt1.google.com/vt/lyrs=y&x={x}&y={y}&z={z}\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "For example, to add Google Satellite as a tile layer:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "29",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "m = geemap.Map()\n",
    "url = \"https://mt1.google.com/vt/lyrs=y&x={x}&y={y}&z={z}\"\n",
    "m.add_tile_layer(url, name=\"Google Satellite\", attribution=\"Google\")\n",
    "m"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "30",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "You can also add text to the map using the `add_text` method. The text will be displayed at the specified location on the map."
